For {= vendor_product =}+ public vendor/product pairs, cover each of the {= evidence_facet =} evidence facets listed below for each pair by supplying {= url =}+ URL per facet. The product must be a DMS, dealership ERP, or dealer-business-system product serving agricultural, construction, forestry, outdoor power, material-handling, rental/fleet, heavy-equipment, powersports, marine/RV, truck, or similar equipment dealers; generic automotive-only DMS, farm-management or agronomy software, ag-input-reseller ERP, CRM/website-only products, and inferred relevance with no dealer-workflow evidence are out of scope.

This is public product/vendor provenance only. Competitive scoring, procurement advice, acquisition analysis, market-share estimates, outreach, contact enrichment, lead scoring, and strategy writing are out of scope.

Evidence facets:
- `official_dealer_product`: a vendor-owned or officially controlled product, industry, documentation, brochure, or platform page that names the product and ties it to equipment or agricultural dealership management.
- `workflow_capability`: a page tying the same product to a concrete dealer workflow or capability, such as parts, inventory, service or work orders, warranty, rental/fleet, wholegoods, finance/accounting, CRM, telematics, OEM interface, reporting, or field service.
- `manufacturer_integration`: a page naming a specific manufacturer/OEM, manufacturer program, interface, certification, approval, or data-exchange function connected to the product. Specific vendor-owned claims count; independent OEM countersignature is not required.
- `dealer_adoption_trace`: a page naming a real dealer/customer/user, dealer story, testimonial, case study, or product-specific public adoption trace. Naked logo walls, generic directories, and broad listicles do not satisfy this facet by themselves.

Requirements:
- The page must clearly identify the named vendor and product, product suite, or product line.
- The page must tie the product to dealership management for an in-scope agricultural, equipment, or adjacent dealer vertical.
- The page must make its facet-appropriate source role visible.
- The page must expose a focused product-specific finding for the selected evidence facet.
